21 SECTION 17.5.(a) G.S. 20-141 is amended by adding a new subsection to read:
22 "(e2) Notwithstanding the speed limits set in subsection (b) of this section or any other
23 provision of law to the contrary, a municipality may, by ordinance, establish a lower default
24 speed limit of not less than 20 miles per hour on streets within the corporate limits of the
25 municipality that are not part of the State highway system. A default speed limit established
26 pursuant to this subsection shall apply to every street within the designated area without requiring
27 the posting of individual speed limit signs on each street segment, provided the municipality
28 erects conspicuous gateway signs at each primary point of vehicular entry into the municipality,
29 or into any defined zone within the municipality, in conformance with the Manual on Uniform
30 Traffic Control Devices, giving notice of the applicable default speed limit. Higher or lower
31 speeds limits posted on individual streets pursuant to subsection (e) of this section shall supersede
32 the default speed limit on those streets. A default speed limit established pursuant to this
33 subsection is effective upon adoption of an ordinance by the municipality and erection of the
34 required gateway signs. The municipality shall maintain a publicly accessible map identifying
35 all streets subject to the default speed limit and all streets on which a different speed limit has
36 been posted pursuant to subsection (e) of this section. Upon written notice from the municipality
37 identifying streets or areas for which a default speed limit has been established pursuant to this
38 subsection, the Department of Transportation shall post the applicable statutory speed limit, not
39 to exceed 35 miles per hour, on State highway system streets, except those designated as part of
40 the Interstate Highway System or other controlled access highway, located within the identified
41 area, unless a different speed limit has been established pursuant to subsection (f) of this section.
42 Nothing in this subsection shall be construed to authorize a municipality to establish or modify
43 speed limits on streets that are part of the State highway system, except as otherwise provided in
44 this section."
