21 Carolina, South Carolina, Tennessee, Virginia, and the following counties in Florida: Bay,
22 Calhoun, Escambia, Gulf, Holmes, Jackson, Okaloosa, Santa Rosa, Walton, and Washington. No
23 invasive species, as determined by the North Carolina Forest Service, may be planted on lands
24 that are part of the State Parks System."
